main event: A round object, described as small like a nickel, was reported moving rapidly at night in Wilmington, Delaware.
interesting points: The object was bright and only visible for about 3 minutes., The sighting occurred while the observer was outside at approximately 2130Z on 9 May 1959., The object moved south to north before disappearing to the east., Many commercial type aircraft were reported in the area at the time., The observer was hesitant to report the sighting but eventually notified base operations.
witness description: Lt. Henry L. Isenberg, 2nd Lt, Officer of the Day
